{title: Cyclone of Rye Cove}
{artist: Doc Watson}
{composer: Written by A.P. Carter and Doc Watson}

[C]Oh listen today to the [F]story I [C]tell
It's saddened with tear dimmed [G7]eyes
Of a [C]dreadful cyclone that [F]came this [C]way
And blew our [G7]schoolhouse [C]away
Rye [F]Cove Rye [C]Cove
The place of my childhood and [G7]home
Where in [C]life's early morn I [F]once loved to [C]roam
But now it's so [G7]silent and [C]lone
When the great storm appeared it [F]darkened the [C]air
And the lightning flashed over the [G7]sky
Then the [C]children all cried don't [F]take us [C]away
But spare us to [G7]go back [C]home
Repeat #3
Oh the mothers so sad and [F]fathers the [C]same
They came to this horrible [G7]scene
Then [C]searching and crying each [F]found their own [C]child
Dying on a [G7]pillow of [C]stone
Lord give us a home far [F]beyond the blue [C]skies
Where storms and cyclones are [G7]unknown
And [C]there will we stand and [F]gladly clasp [C]hands
With our children in their [G7]heavenly [C]home
Repeat #3